                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName ref="#ianuarinus"><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751"><expan><abbr>Fl</abbr><ex>avius</ex></expan> Ianu</supplied>arinus</persName>, <supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751"><expan><abbr>vet</abbr><ex>eranus</ex></expan></supplied>,
                    <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751">de nu</supplied>mero M<supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751">attia</supplied>
                    <lb n="3" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751"><expan><abbr>cor</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan></supplied> <expan><abbr><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751">i</supplied><unclear>u</unclear>nior</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan>, hi<supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751">c posi</supplied>
                    <lb n="4" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751">tus e</supplied>st. Si qu<supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751">is volue</supplied>
                    <lb n="5" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751">rit se</supplied><unclear>p</unclear>ulc<unclear>r</unclear><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751">um eius ape</supplied>
                    <lb n="6" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751">re fisc</supplied>o <choice><reg>dabit</reg><reg>d<supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751">avit</supplied></reg></choice> <supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751">argen</supplied>
                    <lb n="7" break="no"/><supplied reason="lost" evidence="previouseditor" source="#bertolini1874a #bertolini1874b #cilv8751"><measure type="fine" unit="roman_pound" commodity="silver" quantity="10">ti <expan><abbr>lib</abbr><ex>ras</ex></expan> <num value="10">X</num></measure></supplied>.
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p><persName ref="#ianuarinus" xml:lang="la">Flavius Ianuarinus</persName>, a veteran of the <term xml:lang="la">numerus</term> of the <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci iuniores</term>, is laid here.</p>
                <p>Should anyone wish to open his sepulchre, he shall pay ten (Roman) pounds of silver to the <term xml:lang="la">fiscus</term>.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it">
                <p><persName ref="#ianuarinus" xml:lang="la">Flavius Ianuarinus</persName>, veterano del <term xml:lang="la">numerus</term> dei <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci iuniores</term>, qui giace.</p>
                <p>Se qualcuno vorrà aprire il sepolcro di costui, verserà al <term xml:lang="la">fiscus</term> dieci libbre (romane) d'argento.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p>
                    <persName ref="#ianuarinus" xml:lang="la">Flavius Ianuarinus</persName> was a veteran of the <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci iuniores</term>. He chose not to specify his military rank and perhaps remained a <term xml:lang="la">miles</term> (an ordinary soldier) throughout his career. The <term xml:lang="la">auxilium palatinum</term> of the <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci iuniores</term> is recorded as being deployed at times in Gaul (<ref target="../references/bibliography.xml#nd">ND occ. 5, 167; 7, 64</ref>) and at others in the East (<ref target="../references/bibliography.xml#nd">ND or. 6, 53</ref>).
                </p>
                <p>
                    The inscription does not specify the beneficiary of this sarcophagus.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The sarcophagus of <persName ref="#ianuarinus" xml:lang="la">Ianuarinus</persName> was located very close to the northern section of the burial ground. A little further south was the burial of <ref target="./dassiolus.xml"><persName xml:lang="la">Flavius Dassiolus</persName></ref>, another member of the <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci iuniores</term>. Further north, however, was the <term xml:lang="la">arca</term> of a member of the <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci seniores</term>, <ref target="./augustus.xml"><persName xml:lang="la">Flavius Agustus</persName></ref>, the only burial in the northern section of the necropolis that can be identified with certainty as belonging to a soldier.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The arrangement of the <term xml:lang="la">archae</term> suggests that the <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci</term> (both <term xml:lang="la">iuniores</term> and <term xml:lang="la">seniores</term>) were the first <term xml:lang="la">numeri</term> to be permanently stationed in <placeName>Concordia</placeName>. Conversely, the <term xml:lang="la">Batavi</term>, whose burials are concentrated near the southern edge, likely reached the colony at a later stage, characterized by a more massive military presence that led to the creation of distinct burial areas for the various units.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="it">
                <p>
                    <persName ref="#ianuarinus" xml:lang="la">Flavius Ianuarinus</persName> era un veterano dei <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci iuniores</term>. Egli decise di non specificare il proprio grado militare e forse per tutta la sua carriera rimase un <term xml:lang="la">miles</term>, ovvero soldato semplice. L'<term xml:lang="la">auxilium palatinum</term> dei <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci iuniores</term> risulta dislocato ora in Gallia (<ref target="../references/bibliography.xml#nd">ND occ. 5, 167; 7, 64</ref>), ora in Oriente (<ref target="../references/bibliography.xml#nd">ND or. 6, 53</ref>).
                </p>
                <p>
                    Nell'iscrizione non è specificato il dedicatario di questo sarcofago.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Il sarcofago di <persName ref="#ianuarinus" xml:lang="la">Ianuarinus</persName> si trovava molto vicino alla sezione settentrionale del sepolcreto. Poco più a sud era posta la sepoltura di <ref target="./dassiolus.xml"><persName xml:lang="la">Flavius Dassiolus</persName></ref>, un altro membro dei <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci iuniores</term>. Più a nord si trovava invece l'arca di un membro dei <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci seniores</term>, <ref target="./augustus.xml"><persName xml:lang="la">Flavius Agustus</persName></ref>, l'unica sepoltura presente nella sezione settentrionale della necropoli attribuibile con certezza a un militare.
                </p>
                <p>
                    La disposizione delle arche sembra suggerire che i <term xml:lang="la">Mattiaci</term> (sia <term xml:lang="la">iuniores</term> che <term xml:lang="la">seniores</term>) rappresentassero i primi <term xml:lang="la">numeri</term> a stanziarsi stabilmente a <placeName>Concordia</placeName>. Al contrario, i <term xml:lang="la">Batavi</term>, le cui sepolture risultano concentrate presso il margine meridionale, avrebbero raggiunto la colonia in una fase successiva, caratterizzata da una presenza militare più massiccia che portò alla creazione di aree sepolcrali distinte per i vari reparti.
                </p>
